<DIV style="position:absolute;top:103;left:257"><nobr><span class="ft0"><b>Preamble of the Constitution &amp; Bill of Rights</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:145;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft3"><b>Preamble:</b><br>We the People of the United States, in order to form a more perfect Union, establish justice,<br>ensure domestic tranquility [peace], provide for the common defense, promote the general<br>welfare, &amp; secure the blessings of liberty to ourselves and our posterity, do ordain and establish<br>this Constitution for the United States of America.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:270;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft1"><b>Bill of Rights</b></span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:312;left:216"><nobr><span class="ft2">ACTUAL TEXT</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:312;left:621"><nobr><span class="ft2">MEANING</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:355;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">1.  Congress shall make no law respecting</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:355;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Congress cannot set up an official</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:376;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">an establishment of religion, or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:376;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">religion for the country or pass laws</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:396;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">prohibiting the free exercise thereof;</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:396;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">to stop people from following their</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:417;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">or abridging the freedom of speech, or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:417;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">own religion.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:438;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">of the press; or the right of the people</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:438;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Congress cannot make laws that stop</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:459;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">peaceably to assemble, &amp; to petition</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:459;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">people from speaking &amp; writing</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:480;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">the government for a redress of</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:480;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">what they wish.  Congress cannot</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:501;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">grievances.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:501;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft5">make laws that stop people from<br>holding peaceful meetings or from<br>asking the government to correct a<br>wrong action.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:604;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">2.  A well regulated militia being necessary</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:604;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">The people have the right to protect</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:625;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">to the security of a free state, the right of</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:625;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">themselves by serving as armed</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:646;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">of the people to keep and bear arms shall</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:646;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">citizens (militia) and Congress</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:667;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">not be infringed.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:667;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">cannot stop them.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:708;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">3.  No soldier shall, in time of peace be</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:708;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">In peacetime, citizens cannot be</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:729;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">quartered in any house, without the consent</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:729;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">forced to give soldiers a place to</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:750;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">of the owner, nor in time of war, but in a</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:750;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">sleep or meals in their homes.  In</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:771;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">manner to be prescribed by law.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:771;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft5">wartime, this may be done only<br>with federal law.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:832;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">4.  The right of the people to be secure in their</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:832;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">A person cannot be arrested, &amp; his or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:853;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">persons, houses, papers, and effects, against</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:853;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">her house cannot be searched and</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:874;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">unreasonable searches and seizures, shall not</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:874;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">property or papers taken away,</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:895;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">be violated, and no warrants shall issue, but</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:895;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">except with a warrant issued by the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:916;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">upon probable cause, supported by oath or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:916;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Courts.  Whoever asks for a warrant</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:937;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">affirmation, and particularly describing the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:937;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">must explain why, exactly where the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:958;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">place to be searched, and the persons or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:958;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">search is to be made, &amp; who or what</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:978;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">things to be seized.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:978;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">is to be taken.</span></nobr></DIV>
</DIV>
