<DIV style="position:absolute;top:100;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">5.  No person shall be held to answer for a capital,</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:100;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Before anyone can be tried in a</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:121;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">or otherwise infamous crime, unless on a</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:121;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">federal court, a grand jury must</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:141;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">presentment or indictment of a grand jury,</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:141;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">formally accuse that person in an</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:162;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">except in cases arising in the land or naval</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:162;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">indictment, however, this rule does</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:183;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">forces, or in the militia, when in actual service</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:183;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">not apply to the armed forces in</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:204;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">in time of war or public danger; nor shall any</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:204;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">times of war.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:225;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">person be subject for the same offense to be</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:225;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">A person cannot be tried twice for</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:246;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">twice put in jeopardy of life or limb; nor shall</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:246;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">the same crime</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:267;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">be compelled in any criminal case to be witness</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:267;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">No one can be forced to say anything</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:286;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">against himself, nor be deprived of life, liberty,</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:286;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">that would help convict him/herself</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:307;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">or property, without due process of law; nor</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:307;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">The federal government cannot take</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:328;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">shall private property be taken for public use,</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:328;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">away a person’s life, liberty, or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:349;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">without just compensation.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:349;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft5">Property without giving them a fair<br>trial.  This amendment reinforces<br>the belief that people have the right<br>to liberty and ownership of property.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:453;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">6.  In all criminal prosecutions, the accused shall</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:453;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">An accused person has the right to a</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:474;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">enjoy the right to a speedy &amp; public trial, by</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:474;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">prompt, public trial by jury.  The</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:495;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">an impartial jury or the state and district wherein</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:495;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">must be chosen in the state the crime</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:516;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">the crime shall have been committed, which</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:516;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">was committed in.  The accused</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:537;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">district shall have been previously ascertained</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:537;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">must be told of the charges and be</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:558;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">by law, and to be informed of the nature and</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:558;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">present when witnesses speak in</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:577;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">cause of the accusation; to be confronted with</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:577;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">court.  The accused has a right to a</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:598;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">the witnesses against him; to have compulsory</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:598;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">lawyer and has the power to make</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:619;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">process for obtaining witnesses in his favor, and</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:619;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">witnesses come and speak in court</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:640;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">to have the assistance of counsel for his defense.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:640;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">on his behalf.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:682;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">7.  In suits at common law, where the value in</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:682;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">In many disputes that involve more</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:703;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">controversy shall exceed twenty dollars, the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:703;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">than twenty dollars, either side can</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:723;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">right of trial by jury shall be preserved, and no</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:723;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">insist on having a jury trial.  The</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:744;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">fact tried by a jury shall be otherwise re-examined</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:744;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">right of the judges to interfere with</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:765;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">in any court of the United States than according</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:765;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">a jury’s decision is limited to the law</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:786;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">to the rules of the common law.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:828;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">8.  Excessive bail shall not be required, nor</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:828;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Bails, fines, &amp; punishments must not</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:849;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">excessive fines imposed, nor cruel and unusual</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:849;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">be excessive or cruel or unusual</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:868;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">punishment inflicted.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:910;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">9.  The enumeration in the Constitution of certain</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:910;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">The mention of certain rights in the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:931;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">rights shall not be construed to deny or disparage</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:931;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Constitution does not mean they are</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:952;left:131"><nobr><span class="ft2">others retained by the people.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:952;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">The only rights people have.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:994;left:108"><nobr><span class="ft2">10.  The powers not delegated to the United States</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:994;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">The states or the people have all</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:1014;left:140"><nobr><span class="ft2">by the Constitution, nor prohibited by it to the</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:1014;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">powers that have not been assigned</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:1035;left:140"><nobr><span class="ft2">states, are reserved to the states respectively, or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:1035;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">to the federal government or</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:1056;left:140"><nobr><span class="ft2">to the people.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:1056;left:540"><nobr><span class="ft2">Prohibited to the states.</span></nobr></DIV>
</DIV>
